2003 Dodge Caravan w/ 76,500 miles has dead PCM. Dealer is quoting $1100
for repair. This seems very high for unplugging and plugging in a
computer. Can someone please explain the level of work required for this
repair? I understand the PCM is around $450, but why is the install
$650? Also I asked about coverage under the 8/80 Federal Emissions
Regulation and the dealer is denying warrenty coverage, because they are
saying that the problem/diagnoses of the problem did not stem from an
emissions issue. (even though section B of the regulation explicitly
states that manufacture defects/failures are covered)

